  "texts": [
    "Besides this, Lidy and Rauber [36] have evaluated feature sets and fusion strategies for genre classification of music, finding that chroma features are relatively robust to variations in the timbre and dynamics of the signal.",
    "Similarly, citeravanelli2018learning have used chroma features to learn speaker representations for speaker diarization and found that they are robust to noise and reverberation.",
    "Overall, the selection of chroma features for action recognition is justified by their ability to capture the musical and rhythmic structure of an action robustly and effectively.",
    "These characteristics make them a popular choice for many researchers and practitioners in the field.",
    "Proposed methodologyIn this section, we describe our overall proposed framework, which fuses multimodal (audio-image and video) data for action recognition."
